# WebAudit AI Backend Architecture Rule

Follow Feature-Based Architecture with internal layering for all backend changes.

## Required Structure

- Place backend logic in `backend/features/<feature-name>/`.
- For endpoint features, split responsibilities into:
  - `<feature>.route.js` (routing only)
  - `<feature>.controller.js` (HTTP handling + validation)
  - `<feature>.service.js` (business logic / orchestration)
- Keep shared helpers in `backend/utils/`.

## Orchestration Rule

- `backend/features/scan/scan.service.js` is the orchestrator for full scans.
- It calls specialized modules and merges their results.
- Do not put cross-feature orchestration in route or controller files.

## Existing Feature Modules

- `backend/features/puppeteer/puppeteer.service.js`
- `backend/features/seo/seo.service.js`
- `backend/features/lighthouse/lighthouse.service.js`

## Coding Standards

- One clear responsibility per file.
- Use `async/await` for async flows.
- Add explicit error handling and return consistent response shapes.
- Keep modules small, focused, and scalable.
